VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: FILLMORE; 
3 BUILDINGS MAY GET LANDMARK STATUS 
The Fillmore City Council is scheduled to consider declaring three local 
buildings Ventura County landmarks at a meeting today. 
The owners of all three buildings favor the landmark designation, according to 
Katherine Garner of the county Cultural Heritage Board. 
* The United Mercantile Building, built in 1905, now houses the Family Bargain 
Center on Central Avenue. 
* Farmers and Merchants Bank, which dates from 1914, has been home to both 
Security Pacific Bank and Giant Truck Stops and also is on Central Avenue. 
* The former Fillmore Union Grammar School on Sespe Avenue is now used for 
offices by the local school district. The building dates from 1922. JANET 
BERGAMO 
